[
    {
        "content": "<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">module</span><span class=\"o\">!</span>\n<span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">type</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">testModule</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">name</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s\">\"test_module\"</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">author</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s\">\"author\"</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">description</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s\">\"Test module\"</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">license</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s\">\"GPL\"</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"k\">struct</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">TestModule</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;'</span><span class=\"na\">a</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span>\n<span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">module</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kp\">&amp;</span><span class=\"o\">'</span><span class=\"na\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">module</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">modules_names</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nb\">Vec</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">CString</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"k\">fn</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">convert_this_module_to_module</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">module</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kp\">&amp;</span><span class=\"o\">'</span><span class=\"nb\">static</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">ThisModule</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nb\">Result</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;&amp;</span><span class=\"n\">module</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span>\n<span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">unsafe</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"k\">return</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nb\">Ok</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"o\">&amp;</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"o\">*</span><span class=\"n\">this_module</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">as_ptr</span><span class=\"p\">()));</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">};</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"k\">impl</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">kernel</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">Module</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">for</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">TestModule</span>\n<span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">fn</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">init</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">module</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kp\">&amp;</span><span class=\"o\">'</span><span class=\"nb\">static</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">ThisModule</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nb\">Result</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"bp\">Self</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"k\">return</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nb\">Ok</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">TestModule</span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"n\">module</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">convert_this_module_to_module</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">this_module</span><span class=\"p\">),</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">modules_names</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nb\">Vec</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">new</span><span class=\"p\">()});</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>I am getting a ton of errors if I store a reference inside the struct of the module. Do you know why this is happening? Thank you in advance for your time. My goal is to have access only to the module struct that resides inside ThisModule because I find the ThisModule struct hard to use and it always requires the use of unsafe code to get access to the fields inside it.</p>",
        "id": 469017205,
        "sender_full_name": "Theodoros Symeonidis",
        "timestamp": 1725954740
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>What exactly are you trying to do ...?</p>",
        "id": 469017920,
        "sender_full_name": "Alice Ryhl",
        "timestamp": 1725954904
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>You probably shouldn't store a reference to the <code>bindings::module</code> in your module in the first place.</p>",
        "id": 469018041,
        "sender_full_name": "Alice Ryhl",
        "timestamp": 1725954931
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>In my code I am constantly accessing the fields of bindings::module</p>",
        "id": 469018805,
        "sender_full_name": "Theodoros Symeonidis",
        "timestamp": 1725955102
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I don't see a reason why this should be avoided</p>",
        "id": 469018877,
        "sender_full_name": "Theodoros Symeonidis",
        "timestamp": 1725955129
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Neither a reason why I should always unwrap ThisModule</p>",
        "id": 469018953,
        "sender_full_name": "Theodoros Symeonidis",
        "timestamp": 1725955158
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Which fields are you accessing?</p>",
        "id": 469019556,
        "sender_full_name": "Alice Ryhl",
        "timestamp": 1725955297
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Storing an immutable references to <code>bindings::module</code> without wrapping it in <code>Opaque</code> is problematic because it comes with an assumption that the module is immutable. The compiler may optimize under the assumption that reading any field of the module twice results in the same value for both reads, which is probably an incorrect assumption.</p>",
        "id": 469020065,
        "sender_full_name": "Alice Ryhl",
        "timestamp": 1725955401
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Like 50% of the fields.</p>",
        "id": 469020570,
        "sender_full_name": "Theodoros Symeonidis",
        "timestamp": 1725955514
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>you could store the <code>&amp;'static ThisModule</code> directly inside of your struct, that way you don't need to introduce a lifetime to <code>TestModule</code>.</p>\n<p>but if you need to access the fields of <code>struct module</code>, you shouldn't do so directly, instead you should create some abstractions to make them available to safe code.</p>",
        "id": 469022760,
        "sender_full_name": "Benno Lossin",
        "timestamp": 1725956029
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>what driver are you writing this for? something that you plan to upstream?</p>",
        "id": 469022932,
        "sender_full_name": "Benno Lossin",
        "timestamp": 1725956044
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I am not writing a driver for upstream, just a experimenting with linux kernel modules for rust. You first option doesn't sound like a good option because I will need to write a ton of boilerplate code. To be honest I am not so experienced with unsafe rust, and I will have to look into the problem you mentioned. But in general I don't like this solution because of the ton of boilerplate :/</p>",
        "id": 469026853,
        "sender_full_name": "Theodoros Symeonidis",
        "timestamp": 1725957041
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>if you write accessor functions for the <code>ThisModule</code> type, then you don't have a lot of boilerplate, since then you only have to write it once</p>",
        "id": 469027669,
        "sender_full_name": "Benno Lossin",
        "timestamp": 1725957226
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>that's what I meant with abstractions</p>",
        "id": 469027696,
        "sender_full_name": "Benno Lossin",
        "timestamp": 1725957231
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>feel free to post your unsafe code here if you're not confident in it</p>",
        "id": 469027802,
        "sender_full_name": "Benno Lossin",
        "timestamp": 1725957244
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I got to study first a few things, because this link is beyond my level of expertise <a href=\"https://rust-lang.github.io/chalk/book/clauses/opaque_types.html\">https://rust-lang.github.io/chalk/book/clauses/opaque_types.html</a></p>",
        "id": 469028435,
        "sender_full_name": "Theodoros Symeonidis",
        "timestamp": 1725957390
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>By Opaque I'm referring to <a href=\"https://rust.docs.kernel.org/kernel/types/struct.Opaque.html\">https://rust.docs.kernel.org/kernel/types/struct.Opaque.html</a></p>",
        "id": 469029262,
        "sender_full_name": "Alice Ryhl",
        "timestamp": 1725957640
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>That link is something unrelated.</p>",
        "id": 469029290,
        "sender_full_name": "Alice Ryhl",
        "timestamp": 1725957649
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Unfortunately the Opaque type returns a pointer, I want to avoid using pointers, create an intermediate layer for handling all the unsafe code with pointers and then work on top of it using references. So I don't see how Opaque would help me except for creating my own Opaque like type that returns a reference instead of a pointer. I paste bellow a part of my unsafe code module.</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"k\">use</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">kernel</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">bindings</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n<span class=\"k\">use</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">kernel</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">bindings</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"o\">*</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n<span class=\"k\">use</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">kernel</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"kt\">str</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"o\">*</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n<span class=\"k\">use</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">kernel</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"o\">*</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n\n<span class=\"k\">pub</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">fn</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">safe_deref</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;'</span><span class=\"na\">a</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"n\">T</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">ptr</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">*</span><span class=\"k\">const</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">T</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nb\">Option</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;&amp;'</span><span class=\"na\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">T</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">if</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ptr</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">is_null</span><span class=\"p\">()</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"nb\">None</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">}</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">else</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"k\">unsafe</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nb\">Some</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"o\">&amp;*</span><span class=\"n\">ptr</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"k\">pub</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">fn</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">safe_deref_mut</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;'</span><span class=\"na\">a</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">T</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">ptr</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">*</span><span class=\"k\">mut</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">T</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nb\">Option</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;&amp;'</span><span class=\"na\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">mut</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">T</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">if</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ptr</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">is_null</span><span class=\"p\">()</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"nb\">None</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">}</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">else</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"k\">unsafe</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nb\">Some</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"o\">&amp;</span><span class=\"k\">mut</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">*</span><span class=\"n\">ptr</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"k\">pub</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">fn</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">find_module</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">module_name</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kp\">&amp;</span><span class=\"nc\">CString</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nb\">Option</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;&amp;</span><span class=\"n\">module</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span>\n<span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">unsafe</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"k\">return</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">safe_deref</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">bindings</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">find_module</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">module_name</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">as_char_ptr</span><span class=\"p\">()));</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">};</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"k\">pub</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">fn</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">get_task_cred</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">task</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kp\">&amp;</span><span class=\"nc\">mut</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">task_struct</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nb\">Option</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;&amp;</span><span class=\"n\">cred</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span>\n<span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">unsafe</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"k\">return</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">safe_deref</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">bindings</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">get_task_cred</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">task</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">as</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">*</span><span class=\"k\">mut</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">task_struct</span><span class=\"p\">));</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"k\">pub</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">fn</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">list_add</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">list_head</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kp\">&amp;</span><span class=\"nc\">mut</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">list_head</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">other_list_head</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kp\">&amp;</span><span class=\"nc\">mut</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">list_head</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n<span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">unsafe</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"k\">return</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">bindings</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">list_add</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">list_head</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">as</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">*</span><span class=\"k\">mut</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">list_head</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">other_list_head</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">as</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">*</span><span class=\"k\">mut</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">list_head</span><span class=\"p\">);</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"k\">pub</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">fn</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">list_del</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">list_head</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kp\">&amp;</span><span class=\"nc\">mut</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">list_head</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n<span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">unsafe</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"k\">return</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">bindings</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">list_del</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">list_head</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">as</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">*</span><span class=\"k\">mut</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">list_head</span><span class=\"p\">);</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 469033841,
        "sender_full_name": "Theodoros Symeonidis",
        "timestamp": 1725958824
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Please note that I am not sure if this is the correct approach.</p>",
        "id": 469033954,
        "sender_full_name": "Theodoros Symeonidis",
        "timestamp": 1725958855
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>those <code>safe_deref</code> and <code>safe_deref_mut</code> functions are rather strong footguns</p>",
        "id": 469034662,
        "sender_full_name": "Benno Lossin",
        "timestamp": 1725959013
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>if you write proper abstractions for <code>struct module</code>, then it will also have a nice API for users:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"cp\">#[repr(transparent)]</span>\n<span class=\"k\">pub</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">struct</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">Module</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">Opaque</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">bindings</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">module</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"p\">);</span>\n\n<span class=\"k\">impl</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Module</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">pub</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">fn</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">find</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">name</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kp\">&amp;</span><span class=\"nc\">CString</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nb\">Option</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;&amp;</span><span class=\"bp\">Self</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"c1\">// SAFETY: TODO</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"k\">unsafe</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">&amp;*</span><span class=\"n\">bindings</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">find_module</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">name</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">as_char_ptr</span><span class=\"p\">()).</span><span class=\"n\">cast</span><span class=\"p\">()</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>You still need to fill the safety comment todo though.</p>",
        "id": 469035506,
        "sender_full_name": "Benno Lossin",
        "timestamp": 1725959215
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>for using <code>cred</code>, there are some abstractions on the list, so you might just be able to use those: <a href=\"https://lore.kernel.org/rust-for-linux/20240808-alice-file-v9-0-2cb7b934e0e1@google.com/\">https://lore.kernel.org/rust-for-linux/20240808-alice-file-v9-0-2cb7b934e0e1@google.com/</a></p>",
        "id": 469035785,
        "sender_full_name": "Benno Lossin",
        "timestamp": 1725959305
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I am a beginner in Rust (especially unsafe), I haven't found any guidelines of approaching such cases neither any \"quite complex\" kernel modules. My goal isn't to upstream code, my goal is to convert some of my C kernel modules in Rust. But from what I understand a lot of things are missing and maybe upstreaming code is unavoidable.</p>",
        "id": 469036155,
        "sender_full_name": "Theodoros Symeonidis",
        "timestamp": 1725959422
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>yeah a lot of things are missing, so if you are just experimenting, then you can continue to use <code>bindings</code> and <code>unsafe</code> code in your driver.</p>",
        "id": 469036320,
        "sender_full_name": "Benno Lossin",
        "timestamp": 1725959480
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>but if you want to use it in production and/or upstream it, then you should write some abstractions so that you can write mostly safe code in your driver</p>",
        "id": 469036398,
        "sender_full_name": "Benno Lossin",
        "timestamp": 1725959511
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>note that upstreaming abstractions can only happen if you have a user (ie a driver) that you also want to upstream</p>",
        "id": 469036547,
        "sender_full_name": "Benno Lossin",
        "timestamp": 1725959547
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><a href=\"https://lore.kernel.org/rust-for-linux/20240808-alice-file-v9-4-2cb7b934e0e1@google.com/#Z31rust:kernel:cred.rs\">https://lore.kernel.org/rust-for-linux/20240808-alice-file-v9-4-2cb7b934e0e1@google.com/#Z31rust:kernel:cred.rs</a> Also here I see only one field of cred getting exposed you will need to use unsafe again.</p>",
        "id": 469037011,
        "sender_full_name": "Theodoros Symeonidis",
        "timestamp": 1725959653
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"546447\">Benno Lossin</span> <a href=\"#narrow/stream/291565-Help/topic/Storing.20a.20reference.20inside.20the.20struct.20of.20a.20kernel.20module/near/469036547\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>note that upstreaming abstractions can only happen if you have a user (ie a driver) that you also want to upstream</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>The driver is proprietary. But why so many obstacles...</p>",
        "id": 469037350,
        "sender_full_name": "Theodoros Symeonidis",
        "timestamp": 1725959730
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"747876\">Theodoros Symeonidis</span> <a href=\"#narrow/stream/291565-Help/topic/Storing.20a.20reference.20inside.20the.20struct.20of.20a.20kernel.20module/near/469037011\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p><a href=\"https://lore.kernel.org/rust-for-linux/20240808-alice-file-v9-4-2cb7b934e0e1@google.com/#Z31rust:kernel:cred.rs\">https://lore.kernel.org/rust-for-linux/20240808-alice-file-v9-4-2cb7b934e0e1@google.com/#Z31rust:kernel:cred.rs</a> Also here I see only one field of cred getting exposed you will need to use unsafe again.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>yeah, but you can just put it into the <code>cred.rs</code> file and then your driver can use that function without needing <code>unsafe</code></p>",
        "id": 469037616,
        "sender_full_name": "Benno Lossin",
        "timestamp": 1725959798
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"747876\">Theodoros Symeonidis</span> <a href=\"#narrow/stream/291565-Help/topic/Storing.20a.20reference.20inside.20the.20struct.20of.20a.20kernel.20module/near/469037350\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"546447\">Benno Lossin</span> <a href=\"#narrow/stream/291565-Help/topic/Storing.20a.20reference.20inside.20the.20struct.20of.20a.20kernel.20module/near/469036547\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>note that upstreaming abstractions can only happen if you have a user (ie a driver) that you also want to upstream</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>The driver is proprietary. But why so many obstacles...</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>these are the usual conditions for upstreaming C code as well. there is the no dead code rule</p>",
        "id": 469037689,
        "sender_full_name": "Benno Lossin",
        "timestamp": 1725959823
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>for Rust there is just a greater problem, since it's a chicken and egg problem</p>",
        "id": 469037732,
        "sender_full_name": "Benno Lossin",
        "timestamp": 1725959842
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>for C most of the APIs that you would want to use already exist (since they have users)</p>",
        "id": 469037776,
        "sender_full_name": "Benno Lossin",
        "timestamp": 1725959860
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>so if you don't want to learn how to write unsafe code correctly for now, and don't want to upstream your driver, maybe the simplest put is just to \"treat references and pointer as the same\".</p>",
        "id": 469038844,
        "sender_full_name": "Boqun Feng",
        "timestamp": 1725960086
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"546447\">Benno Lossin</span> <a href=\"#narrow/stream/291565-Help/topic/Storing.20a.20reference.20inside.20the.20struct.20of.20a.20kernel.20module/near/469037689\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"747876\">Theodoros Symeonidis</span> <a href=\"#narrow/stream/291565-Help/topic/Storing.20a.20reference.20inside.20the.20struct.20of.20a.20kernel.20module/near/469037350\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"546447\">Benno Lossin</span> <a href=\"#narrow/stream/291565-Help/topic/Storing.20a.20reference.20inside.20the.20struct.20of.20a.20kernel.20module/near/469036547\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>note that upstreaming abstractions can only happen if you have a user (ie a driver) that you also want to upstream</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>The driver is proprietary. But why so many obstacles...</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>these are the usual conditions for upstreaming C code as well. there is the no dead code rule</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>If I create all those abstractions, is there a specific branch that I could place them so that they can help other users (i.e. driver developers that want to upstream their drivers)?</p>",
        "id": 469039146,
        "sender_full_name": "Theodoros Symeonidis",
        "timestamp": 1725960140
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Your driver may have UBs because of this, but it at least can get the ball rolling for you.</p>",
        "id": 469039156,
        "sender_full_name": "Boqun Feng",
        "timestamp": 1725960143
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"411647\">Boqun Feng</span> <a href=\"#narrow/stream/291565-Help/topic/Storing.20a.20reference.20inside.20the.20struct.20of.20a.20kernel.20module/near/469038844\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>so if you don't want to learn how to write unsafe code correctly for now, and don't want to upstream your driver, maybe the simplest put is just to \"treat references and pointer as the same\".</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Then I find little to no point in using Rust for my driver.</p>",
        "id": 469039282,
        "sender_full_name": "Theodoros Symeonidis",
        "timestamp": 1725960182
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>That might be true.</p>",
        "id": 469039334,
        "sender_full_name": "Boqun Feng",
        "timestamp": 1725960197
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>But at least you can start with your \"many unsafe\" driver, and try to remove as much unsafe code as possible.</p>",
        "id": 469039724,
        "sender_full_name": "Boqun Feng",
        "timestamp": 1725960311
    }
]